design.contract_types:
The minimal backend-agnostic contract, INLINE-SCALAR at M16 (the M14 Message::payload precedent). Place in the NEW crates\tb-hal\src\infer.rs. The variable-length neutral core (messages[], tools[], the {cost,speed,intelligence} preference DAG, streamed InferEvents) rides a future M14 channel / M15 block and is DEFERRED exactly as M14 deferred copy_to_user — so the M16 marker needs no pointer.

```rust
/// Resolved model identity = the routing key (index into the const route table).
#[derive(Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)] pub struct ModelId(pub u32);

/// Neutral REQUEST. Inline scalar at M16; args[1..3] reserved for the deferred
/// byte prompt over a block/channel.
pub struct InferRequest { pub model: ModelId, pub prompt: u64 }

/// CLOSED union superset of EVERY backend's finish vocabulary (Anthropic ∩ OpenAI),
/// so no provider distinction is lost when a real adapter lands.
#[derive(Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)] #[repr(u32)]
pub enum StopReason { EndTurn, MaxTokens, StopSequence, ToolUse, Refusal, Pause }

/// Neutral RESPONSE. Collapses Anthropic content[] / OpenAI choices[0] to ONE
/// payload (inline scalar at M16); echoes only the LOGICAL model — backend hidden.
pub struct InferResponse { pub token: u64, pub stop_reason: StopReason }

/// Inference-plane error — DISTINCT from the capability SysStatus (the MCP lesson:
/// model-readable). SysStatus governs dispatch/caps; this governs inference. The
/// facade maps NoBackend -> SysStatus::BadCap at M16.
#[derive(Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]
pub enum InferError { NoBackend, Unavailable, ContextExceeded, Refused, Cancelled }
```

Why these and not more: this is the true intersection a backend MUST carry; provider-only fields (Anthropic top-level `system`/thinking/cache_control/required max_tokens, OpenAI n>1/logprobs/response_format, content-block taxonomy, sampling knobs that even Opus 4.8 now rejects) are the ADAPTER's job and never enter this struct — LiteLLM `drop_params` semantics. The richer non-scalar InferRequest{messages,tools,sampling,prefs} is designed but deferred behind the SAME trait.

design.model_scheme:
The `model:` scheme is the LLM-agnosticity primitive (ARCHITECTURE.md:71 "two provider daemons of the same contract — agnosticity = who registered the scheme"). Grammar + safe parser + longest-prefix router, all in infer.rs.

GRAMMAR (ABNF):
```
model-uri  = "model:" provider [ "/" model-path ] [ "@" version ]
provider   = "mock" / "local" / "anthropic" / "openai" / "auto" / "default" / 1*(ALNUM/"-")
model-path = segment *( "/" segment )      ; "echo" · "llama3" · "gpt-4o" · "llama3/8b-instruct"
version    = 1*(ALNUM/"-"/".")             ; optional pin -> reproducibility, e.g. "claude-opus-4-8"
```
Examples matching the repo: `model:mock/echo` · `model:local/llama3` · `model:anthropic/opus` · pinned `model:anthropic/opus@claude-opus-4-8`. Reserved `model:auto`/`model:default` = pure-preference binding (no provider named → router scores by Prefs+Qos). The PROVIDER segment is the registry key (Fuchsia/Redox typed-scheme prefix-table semantics; no global root, no `..`, prompt-injection path-traversal unrepresentable).

PARSER + ROUTER (safe, no panic):
```rust
/// `model:provider/path[@version]` -> (provider, path). None for a non-model:
/// scheme (so "memory:x"/"block:y" cleanly reject). NEVER panics.
pub fn parse_scheme(uri: &str) -> Option<(&str, &str)> {
    let rest = uri.strip_prefix("model:")?;
    match rest.split_once('/') {
        Some((p, path)) if !p.is_empty() && !path.is_empty() => Some((p, path)),
        None if !rest.is_empty() => Some((rest, "")),   // bare model:auto / model:default
        _ => None,
    }
}
/// Resolve to a registered backend by LONGEST-PREFIX over the route table.
/// None => unknown scheme => clean BadCap at the facade (NEVER a panic).
pub fn resolve(uri: &str) -> Option<(ModelId, &'static dyn InferBackend)> {
    parse_scheme(uri)?;                       // reject non-model: cleanly first
    let mut i = 0;
    while i < ROUTES.len() {
        if ROUTES[i].scheme() == uri { return Some((ModelId(i as u32), ROUTES[i])); }
        i += 1;                               // exact-scheme match suffices for the marker;
    }                                          // production = longest-prefix by provider segment
    None
}
```
TWO-PHASE binding honours the pointer-free [u64;4] ABI: (1) parse+route happens ONCE at session-OPEN (the in-kernel self-test/facade passes the `&str` literal — facades are kernel-side Rust, like agent_block_create taking n_pages; a future EL0 agent passes an interned ModelId token, the deferred string-over-M14/M15 path). (2) INVOKE rides the resulting ModelSession HANDLE, so the scheme is parsed once and the bound backend stays hidden — swap the registered impl behind one prefix → identical agent code = the backend-agnostic contract. ROUTING TABLE: `mock/*`,`local/*`→in-kernel mock (M16 DoD); real `anthropic/*`,`openai/*`→userspace adapters (net egress, EMIT_EXTERNAL-gated, deferred); real `local/*`→vsock to the GPU driver-VM (deferred); `auto`/`default`→router scores by Prefs/Qos (deferred).

design.backend_registry:
The InferBackend trait + the in-kernel registry (the set_hook precedent done WITHOUT unsafe), in infer.rs under `#![forbid(unsafe_code)]`.

```rust
/// A registered backend. The MOCK implements this IN-KERNEL with ZERO unsafe.
/// Real Anthropic/OpenAI/vsock-local adapters implement the SAME trait later in
/// userspace / the driver-VM behind the SAME contract — the agent never sees the
/// impl, only the model: name + the response. Object-safe (no generic methods)
/// so `&'static dyn InferBackend` / `Rc<dyn InferBackend>` is legal in no_std+alloc.
pub trait InferBackend: Sync {
    fn scheme(&self) -> &'static str;                 // longest-prefix routing key
    fn infer(&self, req: &InferRequest) -> InferResponse;   // sync + deterministic at M16
    // DEFERRED: fn invoke_stream(&self, req, out: &mut dyn StreamSink) -> Result<(),InferError>;
    // DEFERRED: fn embed(&self, text:&str) -> Result<Vec<f32>,InferError>;  // fills MemRecord.embedding (T3)
}

/// STATELESS, deterministic loopback — NO clock, NO rng, NO I/O (QEMU has no
/// real net/GPU, so determinism is mandatory for a reproducible CI marker).
/// Stateless => trivially Sync => a `static MOCK` is sound with ZERO unsafe.
pub struct MockBackend { scheme: &'static str }
impl MockBackend { pub const fn new(scheme: &'static str) -> Self { Self { scheme } } }
impl InferBackend for MockBackend {
    fn scheme(&self) -> &'static str { self.scheme }
    fn infer(&self, req: &InferRequest) -> InferResponse {
        InferResponse { token: req.prompt ^ 0xA110_C0DE, stop_reason: StopReason::EndTurn }
    }
}

/// TWO model: names binding ONE contract = the backend-agnostic proof.
static MOCK_CLAUDE: MockBackend = MockBackend::new("model:mock/echo");
static MOCK_LLAMA:  MockBackend = MockBackend::new("model:local/llama3");

/// IMMUTABLE route table: a `static &[&'static dyn InferBackend]` over stateless
/// statics => NO UnsafeCell, NO unsafe. Registration = adding a `static` to this
/// slice. A RUNTIME-mutable router (real userspace/vsock providers) is the
/// DEFERRED dynamic path — the ONLY place a future unsafe could appear (the
/// AGENTS-style UnsafeCell+unsafe impl Sync) — kept OUT of the M16 DoD.
static ROUTES: &[&'static dyn InferBackend] = &[&MOCK_CLAUDE, &MOCK_LLAMA];
```
DELIBERATELY NOT the lib.rs set_trap_hook/IRQ_HOOK precedent (@161-194/706-735) — its transmute is unsafe; the const `&'static` table replaces it with zero unsafe. Object-safety is load-bearing: keep trait methods generic-free or `dyn` breaks.

