design.abi:
Pointer-free, ABI-stable, NO new method numbers, NO new SysStatus — the M11 frozen-boundary invariant holds.

INVOKE (through the M11 chokepoint): SyscallArgs{ method: M_MODEL_INVOKE(=17, already reserved), handle: <ModelSession cap holding INVOKE_MODEL>, args:[prompt_scalar,0,0,0] } -> SysReturn{ Ok, response_scalar } where response_scalar = the bound backend's deterministic InferResponse.token. Gate is FREE from the dispatch prologue: required_right(17)==INVOKE_MODEL (caps.rs:400) → a handle lacking it returns Denied before any body runs.

THE DISPATCH ARM — ADD (do NOT replace the `_ =>` stub; it still serves M_AGENT_SPAWN/M_EMIT_EXTERNAL/M_BUDGET_DELEGATE/M_BLOCK_MAP/M_HANDLE_TRANSFER). Insert immediately BEFORE `_ => SysReturn::ok(0)` (caps.rs:1003), an EXACT clone of the M_BLOCK_READ arm (caps.rs:984):
```rust
// M16: invoke the model session behind `args.handle` (INVOKE_MODEL gated above).
// Clone the Rc<Object> OUT and drop the slot borrow BEFORE calling the backend —
// the single-&mut-at-a-time discipline (M_MEM_*/M_CHAN_*/M_BLOCK_* precedent).
// The router is consulted ONCE at open time, never here, so dispatch keeps
// holding only &mut HandleTable. A non-session cap presented to a model method
// -> BadCap (the M_BLOCK_WRITE wrong-payload branch).
M_MODEL_INVOKE => {
    let obj = match table.slots[i].object.clone() {
        Some(o) => o, None => return SysReturn::err(SysStatus::Stale),
    };
    match &obj.session {
        Some(sess) => SysReturn::ok(sess.invoke(args.args[0]).token),
        None => SysReturn::err(SysStatus::BadCap),
    }
}
```
OUTCOME TABLE: cap with INVOKE_MODEL on a ModelSession -> Ok+token. Cap WITHOUT INVOKE_MODEL -> Denied (prologue, no per-arm code). INVOKE_MODEL on a NON-session object -> BadCap (payload-None branch). Unknown method (e.g. 33, since M_BLOCK_READ=31 is the highest) -> BadMethod (closed set intact). SESSION-OPEN is kernel-mediated (a facade, not an ABI method): the in-kernel self-test names the model via the `model:` &str; a future EL0 agent names it via an interned ModelId token (deferred). The [u64;4] SyscallArgs, the SysStatus closed enum, and the method-number space are ALL untouched — only a payload field + an added arm + a mint helper.

